# Local code-signing config for cetus — COPY to scripts/signing.env (gitignored)
# and fill in. Used by scripts/build-local-signed.sh so that locally-built apps
# carry a STABLE code signature, which is what lets macOS keep your Accessibility
# / Screen Recording grants across rebuilds (ad-hoc signing changes every build,
# so the OS keeps re-prompting — that's the whole reason this exists).
#
# For LOCAL development your free-with-membership "Apple Development" identity is
# enough — it is never notarized, it just needs to be stable. List identities:
#   security find-identity -v -p codesigning
#
# PREFER the 40-char SHA-1 hash over the name: if two certs share a name (e.g. an
# old revoked one + the current one), codesign errors with "ambiguous". The hash
# is unique and never ambiguous. Copy it from the left column of find-identity.
#
# This file (scripts/signing.env) is gitignored. NEVER commit a real identity
# string or any certificate.

APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY="FDD3A9B7D1493248965A09642979A491490600C4"
